				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Delay Death / FM?<a name="68063"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 25 04 3:10 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Don't be so sure Steppy.  I have had a startling increase in the number of times I pop at bind with my emote and Fade going off after I zone.  As near as I can tell, this has only started happening after they changed it to be spell-like.  
<br />

<br />
What seems to happen is that under periods of lots of activity (e.g., raid fights with lots of adds) my fade is not instant.  It isn't even near instant.  I used to be able to click it and instantly see mobs chasing me stop dead in their tracks.  Now I can repeatedly watch them chase for another 2 secs or so.  
<br />

<br />
This is a serious issue in higher end zones where 2 seconds of multi-mob agro is death.  This happened last night in Uqua, with some of the trap mobs charging me.  Just hit the number of the hotkey (no time to use mouse when you need it) and I get about one round of extra combat before they &quot;forget.&quot;
<br />

<br />
If anyone else is seeing this, please post it up.  This was exactly the kind of thing I was leery of when they tweaked our best AA.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
